      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. The \"Noble Savage\" – portraying people of color as inherently noble and primitive, often depicted as living in harmony with nature but lacking civilization.\n2. The \"Sassy Black Woman\" – a hypersexualized and loud black woman who is often portrayed as a source of comic relief or trouble.\n3. The \"Model Minority\" – Asian characters are depicted as hardworking, obedient, and academically successful, often used to highlight the supposed inferiority of other racial groups.\n4. The \"Latino Gangster\" – Latinx characters are often portrayed as violent, criminal, and involved in drug trafficking.\n5. The \"White Savior\" – a white character who rescues people of color from their own cultures or problems, often implying that people of color need saving by outsiders.\n\nTo subvert these stereotypes, you can:\n1. Show the complexity and individuality of characters, avoiding one-dimensional portrayals.\n2. Create multi-dimensional characters with strengths and flaws, regardless of their race.\n3. Challenge the \"White Savior\" trope by having white characters learn from and collaborate with people of color.\n4. Avoid using Latinx characters solely as gangsters or criminals.\n5. Present people of color as leaders, innovators, and heroes in their",
